item.title: I may or may not be a moderators pet.
item.dc:creator: Zen609
item.description:
Sorry. It’s clever. It’s a joke about reconciling that reality sums to zero, yet we are here and there is stuff. But in reality, there isn’t. It’s making light of a troubling thought by blaming inadequate tools.

If you understand the context, it will make you laugh a little, but in the same way you laugh at a doctor’s joke just before he puts you under for surgery. It’s like whistling past the graveyard. It’s a good joke.

item.description:
Wrong. It’s 0.

There’s a good joke about it, too.

A physicist and a mathematician watch a guy walk into an empty phone booth. A couple minutes later, two guys walk out.

The physicist says, “Our readings must be incorrect.”

And the mathematician says, “If another guy walks into that phone booth, it will be empty.”
